text: Mirna Eugenia Ansaldi (born 10 July 1977) is an Argentine volleyball player. She played at the 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2005 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2006 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, and 2008 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup. On club level she played with Gimnasia y Esgrima de Rosario. == References == Category:1977 births Category:Argentine volleyball players Category:Living people
